#balancing the target variable.
#importing libraries for resampling.

from sklearn.utils import resample
df_loanonCardMajority = left_mergeddata[(left_mergeddata['LoanOnCard']==0)]
df_loanonCardMinority = left_mergeddata[(left_mergeddata['LoanOnCard']==1)]

#upsampling the minority class since the gap between the minorityclass and majorityclass is more.

df_minority_upsampled = resample(df_loanonCardMinority,
                                 replace=True,
